  "summary": "Chief Inspector Tsujimura and a group of investigators arrive at the Kyūgajō mansion to examine the crime scene located in the room of Mr. Mikage Itou. The room is a spacious suite filled with antique furniture, situated at the end of a long, dim corridor. Upon entering, the investigators meet Detective Horikawa, Muto, and Detective Horiwell, who is noted as a talented investigator and the right-hand man to Saito Village.\n\nThe investigators discover the body of Itou, an elderly man dressed in a flashy blue woolen robe. The corpse is in a gruesome and bizarre state: the victim has been decapitated, leaving a dark, bloody wound where the head should be, and his feet have also been severed. Muto explains the significance of the missing feet by demonstrating that the victim was wearing decorative medieval iron armor boots. Because these boots are designed for aesthetic purposes rather than practical use, they are too small for human feet to fit inside; consequently, the feet had to be removed to force the victim into the footwear.\n\nThe identity of the victim is confirmed by a silver engagement ring on his right ring finger, which is embedded in his dry skin and engraved with the name \"Ito\" in Roman letters. While the investigators expect a housekeeper to verify the ownership of the ring, they note that the victim's head has not yet been located.",
